task.summary:
Changed the validation length on the password field in the loginform to allow for shorter passwords. Added more info to the repr of Collection.
A lot of stuff in the CollectionView to create new collections and such. Changed the templates to display more info and display the correct forms.
Changed the info on the mainpage depending on if you are logged in or not. Must add csrf_tokens to all forms, wounder if there are any other ways to do it?
Working around the anonymous user that flask-login uses when the user isn't logged in. Should work now with the added is_active calls.

Renamed Group to Collection in __repr__ for Collection so that it actually representes what it is. We do not need to remember the user with cookies, so set it explicitly.
Set the route_base to shorter things, but will probably not keep it. This meant that I had to change the forms since they need to use the correct route.
Also changed the errorhandler for 404 to give a better errormessage for debugging.

Removed the block for the title since that was a little extreme I think, instead it uses justa variable instead. Changed all views and templates to represent this. Changed the register view to not allow the same usernames and at the same time alert you about it.
Removed the Classy logout class since it only needed a simple route, nothing more than that.

Removed the "Du accessade sidan med get istället för post" since it did nothing useful. Changed the layout to always include login/logout things. Started using flask.g to give access to current_user to not have to pass it in to every template, this uses @app.before_request to set up g.user to current_user.
Persistant login/logout ability is very handy and something that just must be there, so it had to be implemented.
Updated the Product and Sprint backlog to better reflect what Im doing. Should start working on the testspecification and such, but it's difficult when there are areas that are missing.

Changed the length of the validators to allow for something to login with it's 5 character password. Added a LinkPostForm to allow for linkposts as well as textposts. Added the LogoutView again since it was having some problems, probably just didn't import it as I should. Changed main.html to user g.user instead of user since it will break if no one is logged in. Added the linkform to to new_post.html. Added the correct url_for since I changed the view.
Working on implementing categories, creating and viewing at first and then posting to them. Created the basic templates but they aren't sufficient since they need to do much more.
